      "content": "The Meridian District is a bit too... rough around the edges for the high-end crowd. I mean, it's a place where you'll find street vendors and night markets, which is just not the kind of atmosphere that says \"refined\" or \"cultured\". And don't even get me started on the diversity - while it's great that the area is welcoming to people from all backgrounds, it's just not the kind of exclusivity that high-net-worth clients are looking for. They want to be seen with people who are just like them, not with people who are... different. Sterling Heights, on the other hand, is a place where you can be sure that everyone is on the same level, culturally speaking.",
